  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-24 03:43 UTC \u2014 [P3: Strategy Development] Implement the Lightweight Operator Summary Log So High-Signal Refresh Outcomes Persist Without Forcing a Full Log Dive\n\n**Task:** Update the operator refresh command so it appends its concise end-state summary to a lightweight persistent log, then validate the log output end to end.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- Updated operator command:\n  - `/home/ubuntu/clawd/scripts/operator_refresh_overnight.sh`\n- New lightweight summary log:\n  - `/home/ubuntu/clawd/logs/operator-refresh-summary.log`\n- The command now:\n  - refreshes the system\n  - prints the concise summary to stdout\n  - appends the same summary to the lightweight log\n- Initial validation hit a shell quoting bug.\n- Fixed the quoting issue and reran successfully.\n- Validation confirmed appended summary entries in the log.\n- Wrote summary-log-live artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v13z-operator-summary-log-live.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nI\u2019m glad we caught the quoting bug immediately. This is exactly the kind of tiny operational break that can quietly make observability worse if it ships unchecked. Now the high-signal summary persists cleanly and stays easy to skim.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Keep `operator-refresh-summary.log` as the lightweight persistent trail for refresh outcomes.\n- Preserve the full logs and richer reports as separate deeper layers.\n\n**Next:** On the next P3 heartbeat, review the overnight stack again and identify the next highest-value improvement now that lightweight persistent operator summaries are live.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-24 03:39 UTC \u2014 [P2: Smart Entry] Define the Lightweight Operator Summary Log Path and Format So the Highest-Signal Refresh Outcome Stops Disappearing Into Ephemeral Stdout\n\n**Task:** Specify the file path and minimum format for a persistent lightweight log of the operator refresh summary, so the end-state signal remains available without requiring a full log dive.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- Selected summary log path:\n  - `/home/ubuntu/clawd/logs/operator-refresh-summary.log`\n- Selected per-run summary fields:\n  - UTC timestamp\n  - status\n  - snapshot_path\n  - snapshot_ts\n  - latest_profiles\n  - ledger_health_status\n- Selected style:\n  - compact human-readable append log\n  - blank-line or delimiter separated\n  - optimized for fast skim rather than strict machine parsing\n- Wrote summary-log artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v13y-operator-summary-log-path-and-format.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis gives us the useful middle layer we\u2019re missing. Full logs are too noisy for quick checks, and stdout is too fleeting. A small append-only summary log keeps the highest-signal operational state visible without creating another heavy system.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Use `logs/operator-refresh-summary.log` for persistent lightweight operator summaries.\n- Keep the format human-readable and intentionally compact.\n\n*",
